         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers0675">
               <p>In <date when="1736">1736</date> Ralph Erskine and his brother
                     <persName>Ebenezer</persName> seceded from the Church of
                     <placeName>Scotland</placeName> to form an &apos;Associate Presbytery&apos;. On
                  the advice of <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2221.xml"/>George
                     Whitefield</persName>, <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"
                     />JW</persName> wrote to Erskine in <date when="1739">1739</date>, seeking
                  advice about guiding the revival in <placeName>Bristol</placeName>. While Erskine
                  was of some help, his staunch Calvinism soon led to an end of the correspondence.
                  See <hi rend="italic">DEB</hi>, 363–64; and <hi rend="italic">ODNB</hi>.</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
